word_mean_info__list.difference: 委婉用词。从本义“从肺部吐出气来”引申为吐出最后一口气，断气而死。
书面用词，多指夭折或不幸暴亡。
最普通用词，指某人或某物失去生命而永远不存在。
正式用词，多指法律上的用语。

bilingual.source: This agreement doesn't expire and cannot be cancelled.
bilingual.target: 协议没有终止时间也不能取消。

bilingual.source: All the Bush tax cuts are set to expire on Dec . 31.
bilingual.target: 一切布什的减税计划都将于12月31号终止.

bilingual.source: So will your hopes, ambitions, plans and to do lists expire too.
bilingual.target: 你的希望，抱负，计划和安排同样会终止。

bilingual.source: Sorrows maybe could be healed by time, but it will never expire.
bilingual.target: 时间可以治愈悲伤，但它将永远不会终止。

bilingual.source: The facility will expire on such date as specified in the facility letter.
bilingual.target: 此项透支服务将在有关信贷文件中的指定日期终止。

bilingual.source: Article 10 Labor contracts terminate when their operation terms expire or conditions on which both parties agree to terminate the contracts appear.
bilingual.target: 劳动合同期满或双方约定的终止条件出现，劳动合同即行终止。

bilingual.source: So Mr.Bush evaded the rules by making the tax cut temporary, with the whole thing scheduled to expire on the last day of 2010.
bilingual.target: 因此，布什给那个减税法案设立了一个期限，也就是在2010年的最后一天终止，从而规避了参议院的典章制度。

bilingual.source: So Mr. Bush evaded the rules by making the tax cut temporary, with the whole thing scheduled to expire on the last day of 2010.
bilingual.target: 因此，布什给那个减税法案设立了一个期限，也就是在2010年的最后一天终止，从而规避了参议院的典章制度。

bilingual.source: It would let Bush-era tax cuts for upper income earners expire, limit deductions for wealthier filers and close loopholes and end some corporate tax breaks.
bilingual.target: 计划将让布什期间的针对高收入人士的税收减让政策期满失效，限制富裕申报人的税前扣除，关闭税收漏洞，终止某些公司所得税减免。
他的签证将在下个月到期。

list.abstract: vi.期满；文件、协议等（因到期而）失效；断气；逝世第三人称单数：expires过去式：expired过去分词：expired现在分词：expiring VERB到期；期满；失效When something such as a contract,deadline,or visa expires,it comes to an end or is no longer valid.He had lived illegally in the United States for five years after his visitor's visa expired.在访问签证到期后，他又在美国非法居住了5年。VERB气绝；死亡；He endured excruciating agonies before he finally expired.在最终离世前他经受了极大的痛苦。

yingyinNormal.en: But next month, its charter will expire unless Members of Congress do their job and reauthorize it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但下个月，这些帮助就没有了，除非国会议员们通过法案对该银行重新授权。

yingyinNormal.en: And you know this pass I was given. Well, these passes, they have a date on them, a date when they expire.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我拿到的这张通行证，原本是有使用期限的。

exam_freq_info.chinese: 满期; 届期; 终止

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: 5bn programme of grants to fund new affordable housing, set to <highlight>expire</highlight> in 2015, is unlikely to be extended beyond then.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一项资助新建经济适用房的50亿英镑拨款计划将于2015年到期，此后不太可能延长。
